Text: For most women, birth control is completely safe. Some women might experience some side effects like spotting or cramping but they usually go away as the body adjusts. For most of us, the benefits of birth control are way more important than a few side effects. And you might not know this but, some kinds of birth control actually protect against certain types of cancers!

Text: how do i make an appointment

If you're thinking about starting birth control, you should definitely talk to your doctor about your options. If you don’t have a regular doctor or don’t feel comfortable visiting them, you can also visit places like Planned Parenthood or Family Planning Service. They know alllllll about birth control and can let you know everything you need. For Planned Parenthood, you should even be able to make an appointment online.
